pipeline_summary.name: regulatory_report_router
pipeline_summary.description: This regulatory reporting pipeline processes financial transaction data and routes it to appropriate regulatory systems based on account type, following a branchmerge pattern. It extracts CSV data, branches processing for international (FATCA) and domestic (IRS) accounts, runs parallel reporting workflows, and merges results for archival.

components.name: Extract Transaction CSV
components.description: Reads financial transaction CSV files from the local filesystem and makes the processed data available via XCom for downstream analysis.
outputs: XCom object `csv_data_processed` containing parsed transaction records

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; first step in the pipeline.

components.name: Determine Account Routing
components.description: Analyzes transaction records to decide whether each record should be routed to FATCA (international) or IRS (domestic) reporting paths.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful extraction of CSV data.

components.name: Generate FATCA Report
components.description: Processes international account transactions to produce a FATCAcompliant XML report and publishes a generation status via XCom.
inputs: XCom object `csv_data_processed` filtered for international accounts

upstream_policy.description: Executes when the routing decision selects the FATCA path.

components.name: Generate IRS Report
components.description: Processes domestic account transactions to produce an IRS 1099style JSON report and publishes a generation status via XCom.
inputs: XCom object `csv_data_processed` filtered for domestic accounts

upstream_policy.description: Executes when the routing decision selects the IRS path.

components.name: Archive Regulatory Reports
components.description: Merges FATCA XML and IRS JSON reports, compresses them, and stores the archive in a secure location for compliance retention.
inputs: FATCA XML report file from generate_fatca_report
IRS JSON report file from generate_irs_report
outputs: Compressed archive file (e.g., ZIP) containing all regulatory reports

upstream_policy.description: Runs after both FATCA and IRS report generation tasks have completed, regardless of their success status.

connections.purpose: Store the final compressed archive of regulatory reports

description.description: Comprehensive description of the regulatory reporting pipeline
description.default: This regulatory reporting pipeline processes financial transaction data and routes it to appropriate regulatory systems based on account type, following a branchmerge pattern. It extracts CSV data, branches processing for international (FATCA) and domestic (IRS) accounts, runs parallel reporting workflows, and merges results for archival.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

sources: CSV transaction files stored on the local filesystem (e.g., /data/transactions/*.csv)
sinks: Secure archive storage (S3 bucket 'regulatory-archive') containing the archived regulatory reports
